OneDrive setup (optional)
To use OneDrive, set these environment variables for the backend and create an Azure AD app with Application permission Files.ReadWrite.All:
ONEDRIVE_TENANT_ID – Azure AD tenant id
ONEDRIVE_CLIENT_ID – App (client) id
ONEDRIVE_CLIENT_SECRET – Client secret
ONEDRIVE_DRIVE_ID – Target OneDrive (or SharePoint) drive id
In Settings, set Skill photos folder to the folder path inside that drive (e.g. Skills/Photos). Without these env vars, photos are stored locally and still work via the Open link.